ggplot(data = diam) +
  geom_point(mapping = aes(x = carat, y = price))

Statistical Transformations: stat

  • x (count) sum_data cut (count)

    sum_data <- diam %>% 
  group_by(cut) %>%
  summarise(count = n())

sum_data
    #> # A tibble: 5 x 2
#>   cut       count
#>   <ord>     <int>
#> 1 Fair         34
#> 2 Good        146
#> 3 Very Good   350
#> 4 Premium     377
#> 5 Ideal       593

  • sum_data geom_bar() x geom_bar() stat

  • geom_bar() stat "count" geom_bar() x

  • data frame stat "identity" mapping data frame y 

    # stat = "identity"
ggplot(data = sum_data) +
  geom_bar(mapping = aes(x = cut, y = count),
           stat = "identity") +
  labs(title = 'stat = "identity"')

# stat = "count" (geom_bar )
ggplot(data = diam) +
  geom_bar(mapping = aes(x = cut),
           stat = "count") +
  labs(title = 'stat = "count" (default)')

geom_*() stat

  • geom_*() stat
    • geom_point() stat = "identity" x y mapping data frame x y
    • geom_bar() stat = "count" x y

Position Adjustments: position

ggplot(data = diam) +
  geom_bar(aes(x = cut, fill = cut))

ggplot(data = diam) +
  geom_bar(aes(x = cut, fill = clarity))

# position: stack (default)
ggplot(data = diam) +
  geom_bar(aes(x = cut, fill = clarity),
           position = "stack")

# position: fill
ggplot(data = diam) +
  geom_bar(aes(x = cut, fill = clarity),
           position = "fill")

# postion: dodge
ggplot(data = diam) +
  geom_bar(aes(x = cut, fill = clarity),
           position = "dodge")

ggplot(mpg) +
  geom_point(aes(class, hwy))
